subject: re: ANN: test your JUnit 3.8/4.0 skills
msgSnippet: Todd, ... These exams are free and were written by volunteers.  I would love to hear your feedback on how the JUnit exams could be improved - either here, by
messageBody:
Todd,
> I don't know anything about javablackbelt.com, but I
> hope you're not going to charge anyone money to take
> that test as it's currently written
These exams are free and were written by volunteers. I would love to
hear your feedback on how the JUnit exams could be improved - either
here, by e-mail or in the JavaLobby forum.

Neil,
> I know the best way to improve this is to submit questions myself and
> comment on the others but I suspect a lot of the community like it
> just the way it is.
I don't think anyone on the site is intending for there to be trick
questions! I certainly don't. Again, feel free to comment. I
personally am moderator for these JUnit exams and would definitely
take such comments seriously to improve the exam.

Thanks,
Jeanne
